{"parse":{"title":"Pubilla","pageid":28548795,"revid":850707465,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pubilla1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/Pubilla1.jpg/220px-Pubilla1.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/Pubilla1.jpg/330px-Pubilla1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/Pubilla1.jpg/440px-Pubilla1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"733\" data-file-height=\"550\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pubilla1.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Formal naming of a pubilla during a ceremony in <a href=\"/wiki/Solsona,_Lleida\" title=\"Solsona, Lleida\">Solsona</a></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG/220px-Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"266\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG/330px-Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG/440px-Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"1216\" data-file-height=\"1472\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pubilles-Ulldecona7.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Pubilles in <a href=\"/wiki/Ulldecona\" title=\"Ulldecona\">Ulldecona</a>.</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>pubilla</b> (<small>Catalan pronunciation:&#160;</small><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:IPA/Catalan\" title=\"Help:IPA/Catalan\">[pu\u02c8\u03b2i\u028e\u0259]</a></span>; plural <i>pubilles</i>) in ancestral <a href=\"/wiki/Catalan_tradition\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Catalan tradition\">Catalan tradition</a> was the female that would inherit the whole rural estate  in the absence of a brother.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Tradition\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Tradition</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Literature\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Literature</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Tradition\">Tradition</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pubilla&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Tradition\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>She was the female version of the <a href=\"/wiki/Heir\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Heir\">hereu</a> or male heir of the whole property of the family. Traditionally, when a couple had no son, the eldest girl of the family would inherit the home and the estate in ancient <a href=\"/wiki/Catalonia\" title=\"Catalonia\">Catalonia</a>. The purpose was not to divide estates that were already too small to exploit in a profitable manner.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>From mid 20th century onwards the image of the pubilla underwent a change; in present times the pubilla has a role similar to a local <a href=\"/wiki/Beauty_queen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Beauty queen\">beauty queen</a> in local popular celebrations.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nSometimes the female <i><a href=\"/wiki/Gegants\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gegants\">gegants</a></i> are dressed as a pubilla, like in <a href=\"/wiki/Manresa\" title=\"Manresa\">Manresa</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Often the naming of a pubilla is a good occasion for a Catalan girl to dress in the traditional costume.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pubilla&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Traditions_of_Catalonia\" title=\"Traditions of Catalonia\">Traditions of Catalonia</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Symbols_of_Catalonia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Symbols of Catalonia\">Symbols of Catalonia</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ciutat_Pubilla_de_la_Sardana&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ciutat Pubilla de la Sardana (page does not exist)\">Ciutat Pubilla de la Sardana</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pubilla&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jstor.org/pss/3773351\">JSTOR: Corporate Household and Ecocentric Kinship Group in Catalonia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.elpunt.cat/noticia/article/2-societat/5-societat/83241-ambaixadors-del-seu-poble.html?piwik_campaign=rss&amp;piwik_kwd=canals\">Una pubilla no \u00e9s una \"miss\"</a> d'Ariadna Ventura, publicat a <i><a href=\"/wiki/El_Punt\" title=\"El Punt\">El Punt</a></i> del 30 de setembre de 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mainlymorrisdancing.org.uk/Giants/manresa.html\">Pubilla gegant</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20100817145100/http://www.mainlymorrisdancing.org.uk/Giants/manresa.html\">Archived</a> 2010-08-17 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.pubillatge.com/public/php/auques/auca_dela_pubilla/\">Auca de la pubilla</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20070717070600/http://www.pubillatge.com/public/php/auques/auca_dela_pubilla/\">Archived</a> 2007-07-17 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Literature\">Literature</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pubilla&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Literature\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Kathryn_Woolard\" title=\"Kathryn Woolard\">Kathryn A. Woolard</a>, <i>Double talk: bilingualism and the politics of ethnicity in Catalonia</i>, Stanford University Press (1989), <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8047-1502-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-8047-1502-7\">978-0-8047-1502-7</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pubilla&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Catego